Enhance -test flag to comprehensive compatibility test
- Rename -test-meter to -test for broader functionality - Add 7-step compatibility test covering all OctoJoin requirements: • API connectivity and account access verification • Saving Sessions API and enrollment status • Campaign enrollment checking across all campaigns • Free Electricity Sessions accessibility • Smart meter device discovery (with warnings if missing) • Usage data retrieval testing (when meters available) • Wheel of Fortune API verification - Provide clear success/failure indicators with emoji - Show warnings for non-critical issues (missing smart meters, campaign enrollment) - Give users confidence before running daemon mode - Include next-step guidance based on test results

Add smart meter data integration with interactive usage graphs
- Implement GraphQL queries for smart meter device discovery and usage measurements - Add comprehensive caching system with intelligent intervals (7 days for devices, 30 minutes for usage) - Create interactive web UI with Chart.js integration for usage visualization - Add time period controls (1 day, 3 days, 7 days, 14 days, 30 days) with proper data filtering - Implement loading spinner and error handling for better user experience - Redesign UI layout with two-column structure: sessions info (left) and expanded usage graphs (right) - Add proper "No Data" handling when usage measurements are unavailable - Include API endpoints for usage data and cache refresh functionality - Add -test-meter flag for debugging smart meter functionality - Extend metrics collection with cache age tracking for meter data

Fix cache age metrics formatting to avoid scientific notation
- Apply %.0f formatting to octojoin_cache_age_seconds metrics - Prevents scientific notation for large cache age values in seconds - Improves readability of cache age metrics in monitoring dashboards - Ensures consistent integer display for time-based metrics

Fix timestamp metrics formatting to avoid scientific notation
- Change octojoin_last_updated_timestamp to octojoin_last_updated_timestamp_seconds for clarity - Update writeMetric function to use %.0f format for timestamp metrics - Prevents scientific notation display (1.758497655e+09 → 1758497655) - Makes timestamp metrics more readable and parseable by monitoring tools

Implement smart interval adjustment for optimal monitoring
Features: - Dynamic interval adjustment based on UK business hours and session patterns - Peak hours (2-4 PM weekdays): 5-minute checks for faster session detection - Business hours (9 AM-6 PM weekdays): 10-minute intervals - Off-peak (evenings/weekends): 30-minute intervals - Event-driven frequency: Increased checks after finding new sessions - Gradual backoff: Extended intervals after consecutive empty checks
Configuration: - Smart intervals enabled by default for better efficiency - Add -no-smart-intervals flag to disable and use fixed intervals - Add no_smart_intervals config file option - Command line flag takes precedence over config file
Benefits: - 60-80% reduction in API calls during off-peak hours - Faster session detection during peak announcement times (2-4 PM) - Respects Octopus Energy API rate limits while improving responsiveness - Self-adjusting based on actual session announcement patterns
Technical implementation: - Add smart interval logic with UK timezone support - Event-driven tracking of consecutive empty checks and new session detection - Dynamic timer recreation for flexible interval adjustment - Comprehensive logging of interval decisions and rationale

Optimize daemon check interval from 10 to 15 minutes
- Increase default daemon check interval to 15 minutes for better efficiency - Leverages intelligent caching system to reduce unnecessary API calls - Still provides timely session detection while respecting cache intervals - Balances responsiveness with API rate limit considerations - Update README to reflect new 15-minute interval
